hat вЂ‹is the fundamental pieces to this problem? вЂ‹And do I have existing patterns that I know вЂ‹about that I can use to hopefully tackle all of it, вЂ‹but if I can't tackle all of it, вЂ‹can I use patterns and apply вЂ‹them to as many different pieces as possible so вЂ‹that your unknown piece that you really have to вЂ‹start from scratch and invent something new? вЂ‹That it's as small as possible, вЂ‹that we can start with as many pieces as possible with вЂ‹a roadmap for them a pattern to вЂ‹apply. That's what we're going to be doing. вЂ‹Now it may start to seem more complicated than it is, вЂ‹but at the end of the day, вЂ‹what we're still doing is we're вЂ‹still building up language. вЂ‹We're still writing in natural language, вЂ‹we're still writing sentences вЂ‹, we're still communicating. вЂ‹We're just thinking intentionally вЂ‹about the patterns in our language. вЂ‹And we're thinking about what are the statements in вЂ‹the organization of this statements вЂ‹in order to solve the problem. вЂ‹In some ways, combining patterns is вЂ‹really doing a more powerful version of programming. вЂ‹We're starting to take вЂ‹different programs are вЂ‹instructions that we know how to use вЂ‹and put them together in вЂ‹more complex and sophisticated ways вЂ‹in order to have prompts that have more power to them, вЂ‹they have more depth to them. вЂ‹Again, don't feel that this is something you can't do, вЂ‹everybody can do this. вЂ‹At the end of the day, think about it. вЂ‹You're just describing in words what you want done. вЂ‹You're still describing in вЂ‹language what you're trying to accomplish. вЂ‹All this is doing is helping us think вЂ‹about what should go into the instructions. вЂ‹If we're going to use this pattern, вЂ‹it's giving us a set of commands, вЂ‹a set of statements that we need вЂ‹to include and an organization for them. вЂ‹If we're going to use this pattern, вЂ‹we're going to have a set of вЂ‹statements that we're going to include. вЂ‹Oftentimes, putting things together вЂ‹is simple as just taking вЂ‹the statements from each pattern and вЂ‹making sure they all show up in the prompt. вЂ‹Sometimes it's that simple, вЂ‹sometimes it's more nuanced and we made need to make вЂ‹sure a certain statement ends up in a certain place. вЂ‹Like what they asked for input pattern, вЂ‹we probably always want вЂ‹the ask for input to show up at the end of the prompt, вЂ‹because otherwise it doesn't work nearly as effectively. вЂ‹Although putting patterns together вЂ‹can be a little bit tricky sometimes вЂ‹if you have to figure out where things should go, вЂ‹most of the time, вЂ‹it's as simple as putting the statements together. вЂ‹As we go through the rest of the course, вЂ‹what I would encourage you to do is to notice when вЂ‹I'm using multiple patterns together to вЂ‹solve a problem and to think about as you're вЂ‹trying to tackle new tasks with prompt engineering, вЂ‹how to use multiple patterns in вЂ‹conjunction with each other to solve the problem.\"}